The following are presented in no particular order, although some items need to happen before others can occur.
These are needed for each linux hardening script.

1. Add default distro repos
2. Update all packages
3. run nmap (pipe into file for later use)
4. block unnecessary open ports (iptables)
5. shut down unneeded processes
6. Install htop (or other similar?)
7. Remove all unnecessary shell access for users
8. Install 7zip for encrypting sensitive data
9. Crawl to find interesting files?
